summary: My Apollonyaa with 7B Body and optional UnpB Body, ADEC Body and CBBE Body ( without Tattoos ). Blue Eyes or Pink Eyes. And now as a Vampire with pink Eyes. But she looks a bit different. I had to re create her.
descriptionHtml:
[size=3]

[/size][img]https://i.imgur.com/CekyWHf.jpg[/img]
Picture made by rcreaper2
[font=Georgia][color=#ff00ff][size=4][i]This is my Apollonyaa with 7B Body and optional UnpB Body, ADEC Body and
CBBE Body ( without Tattoos ). Pink or blue Eyes. And now as a Vampire
with pink Eyes. But she looks a bit different and she has a different
last name. So you can have both in the game! I had to re create her.[/i][/size][/color][/font]

[font=Georgia][color=#a64d79][size=4][i]This is my first Standalone Mod[/i][/size][/color][/font]

[font=Georgia][color=#c27ba0][size=4][i]Location:[/i][/size][/color][/font]
[font=Georgia][color=#d5a6bd][size=3][i]Apollonyaa Apo-Nord Wizard/Levl.10: You find Apollonyaa in the Winterholdcollege Hall of the Elements.[/i][/size][/color][/font]
[img]https://i.imgur.com/mvcJUJM.jpg[/img]
[img]https://i.imgur.com/KKPXUI8.jpg[/img]
[img]https://i.imgur.com/7x3L1y2.jpg[/img]
[img]https://i.imgur.com/qaU3NJy.jpg[/img]



[font=Georgia][color=#d5a6bd][size=4][i]Recommend:[/i][/size][/color][/font]

[font=Georgia][color=#ead1dc][size=3][i]XP32 Maximum Skeleton -XPMS by xp32[/i][/size][/color][/font]

[font=Georgia][color=#ff00ff][i][size=3]YOU NEED THIS OR ELSE YOU WILL CRASH TO THE DESKTOP!!![/size][/i][/color][/font]

[font=Georgia][color=#d5a6bd][size=4][i]Does not replace anything in Game!![/i][/size][/color][/font]

SG Hairs

[font=Georgia][color=#ff00ff][size=4][i]Recommend:[/i][/size][/color][/font]
[i][size=5][font=Georgia][color=#a64d79][size=3]For All BBP_TBBP Versions: These body options do have extra requirements refer to those mod pages if you need extra help
-NOTE: To run any BBP/TBBP-Body version Mod properly, you have to install a
skeleton which supports BBP or TBBP such as XP32's XP32 Maximum
Skeleton, which is what i have used. If not you'll get a crash at
startup.
There are several skeleton/animation/package options out there to choose from.[/size][/color][/font]
[/size][/i]


[font=Georgia][color=#ff00ff][size=4][i]Manually Installation:[/i][/size][/color][/font]
[font=Georgia][color=#c27ba0][size=3][i]Copy the ESP, Meshes and Textures-Folder[/i]
[i]and paste it in your Data- Folder,[/i]
[i]and confirm to overwrite if you already[/i]
[i]have a Meshes and Textures Folder there.[/i][/size][/color][/font]
